abstract: A week into a federal auction for wireless licenses, Google found itself at risk of being the winning bidder for the coveted spectrum.
snippet: A week into a federal auction for wireless licenses, Google found itself at risk of being the winning bidder for the coveted spectrum.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO  Google had little desire to own a premium slice of the nation’s airwaves, but a week into a federal auction for wireless licenses, it found itself at risk of being the winning bidder for the coveted spectrum.

headline.main: An Auction That Google Was Content to Lose
headline.print_headline: An Auction That Google Was Content to Lose
